Pollio was among Caesar’s generals when he crossed the Rubicon, and at the battle of Pharsalia. After Caesar’s death he joined M. Antony‚ and sided with him in the Peru- sian war. He remained neutral after the battle of Actium. Indeed he retired from an active share in public life after his · victorious expedition against the Parthini, an Illyrian people bordering on Dalmatia, and it is to that victory which Horace refers as the “ Dalmatian triumph.” He then gave
